item.title: Please help
item.dc:creator: @Scape-JAVA Scape-JAVA
item.description:
@Scape-JAVA wrote:

You can check in the config class and see if there’s an array or a string that has something to do with it. You can also check the commands class to see if the previous developer just allowed every command for him i.e: he did this

if(playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("givedonor") && c.playerName.equals("Gabbe")) {

He could of done something like that, just change the name, or remove it.

item.title: Please help
item.dc:creator: @Scape-JAVA Scape-JAVA
item.description:
@Scape-JAVA wrote:

You have to change your character rights in the characters folder.

And you can change the command by going into the commands class and editing who has the permission to give the donator rank to players. You can also remove the vulgar remark as well. The givedonor command should be under the function [tt]ownerCommands[/tt]
